body:
### Version

0.59+130

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

1. Create the following plugin:
```c
#include "kernel/yosys.h"

USING_YOSYS_NAMESPACE
PRIVATE_NAMESPACE_BEGIN

struct HelloWorldPass : public Pass {
    HelloWorldPass() : Pass("hello_world", "print modules in design") { }

    void help() override
    {
        // Called when user runs:   help hello_world
        log("Usage: hello_world\n");
        log("Prints the names of all modules in the current design.\n");
    }

    void execute(std::vector<std::string> args, RTLIL::Design *design) override
    {
        log_header(design, "Executing HELLO_WORLD pass.\n");

        if (args.size() != 1) {
            log_cmd_error("This pass takes no arguments.\n");
        }

        log("Modules in current design:\n");
        for (auto module : design->modules()) {
            if (!design->selected(module))
                continue;
            log("  %s\n", log_id(module));
        }
    }
} HelloWorldPass;

PRIVATE_NAMESPACE_END
```

2. Compile with: `yosys-config --build hello.so hello.cc`

3. Export LD library: `export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$PWD`

4. Run with: `yosys -m ./hello.so -p "hello_world"`

5. Yosys returns the following error:
```sh
Yosys 0.59+130 (git sha1 c43246bba, clang 18.1.3 -fPIC -O3)
yosys: symbol lookup error: ./hello.so: undefined symbol: _ZN5Yosys4PassC2ENSt7__cxx1112basic_stringIcSt11char_traitsIcESaIcEEES6_
```

### Expected Behavior

Plugin prints `Hello World` to console

### Actual Behavior

```sh
Yosys 0.59+130 (git sha1 c43246bba, clang 18.1.3 -fPIC -O3)
yosys: symbol lookup error: ./hello.so: undefined symbol: _ZN5Yosys4PassC2ENSt7__cxx1112basic_stringIcSt11char_traitsIcESaIcEEES6_
```

